title: For Sale/Trade:  Taurus Model 80 Revolver with holster and ammo
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is an early Taurus Model 80 in .38 Special, from either the late 1970s or the early 1980s.  The Taurus Model 80 is a clone of the S&W Model 10.  It has a 4" barrel, six shot cylinder, blued finish, and wood grips.

The mechanism locks up strong and works perfectly, and the bore is excellent. I've only shot it a few times since I got it several years ago, and it doesn't look to have seen much use at all before that.  Unfortunately, it was subjected to a couple decades of less than ideal storage by a previous owner, so there are some rust spots on the bluing.  

But this gun has a ton of potential.

Most of the rust is on the rear of the grip, which had turned the bluing into patina there. It looks like someone gripped the revolver, then stuck it in storage without oiling it properly. It would benefit from some TLC with a bronze brush and gun oil.  And if need be, you could potentially reblue the rust area, or the entire handgun could be refinished with something like Cerakote.

Also included with the revolver is a vintage Don Hume leather holster, along with 40 rounds of Remington FMJ and 70 rounds of Remington jacketed hollow point .38 special ammo.  (110 rounds total.)

$200 cash, or I'm looking to trade for a military surplus rifle or handgun, or a gun safe.

Feel free to email me through the Armslist contact form, or text me at four 7 nine - two 8 three - three 7 7 nine.

title: For Sale:  Schmidt and Bender 3-20x50 PMII LP MSR
postcontent:
ENABLE TO CONTACT ME @      see_maye@yahoo.com


The Schmidt & Bender PMII outperforms every competitive scope in so many ways it is hard to know where to begin. This Schmidt and Bender scope has a nice solid feel and construction. Everything has a very uniform finish, tight tolerances and just excellent quality everywhere. The tube is a 34mm tube, which is becoming a more common tube diameter. There are many ring / mount manufacturers that make 34mm rings, so mounting for this particular scope was effortless. All of the moving parts are precise and smooth. The power adjust ring is very easy to grip and does not require a whole lot of effort to adjust, which is actually a little less common than you might think. There is a typical fast focus eye piece (diopter adjustment), which works wonderfully. The tube is a solid one piece tube, as you would expect, and the exterior finish is an exceptional anodized coating. The eye relief on the scope is also generous providing ample room to use the scope on high recoiling rifles without problem, and it easily covers a wide range allowing for quick full sight picture alignment.Of course, when you pay the big dollars for a S&B scope, the thing you are paying for is the optical quality, and this scope does not disappoint. The optics on the scope are exceptional

title: For Sale:  Dye Precision Rotor Paintball Loader - Red
postcontent:
The Dye Rotor is the most radical innovation in paintball loader technology fusing simplicity with mind blowing feed rates and reliability. It is easy to see why the Rotor has become the number one choice in loader technology among top level player's worldwide. 

The Rotor™ is the most energy-efficient loader in the sport, boasting a battery life of over 80,000+ ball shot count with only 3 AA batteries. The Rotor™ features a positive push button with a bright LED display informing you of when your hopper is powered on or off. The Dye Rotor system has a variety of upgrades such as color kits, quick feeds and high capacity tops. 

Low Profile Design

The Rotor™ is already one of the lightest 200-round loaders available; we've now equipped it with Low-Profile Design, a unique design that pushes balls straight down over a short distance, allowing for a small loader size and shape and an extremely low profile.

Tuff Molding

The Rotor™ is constructed with Dye's proprietary Tuff™ Molding, In testing, we found that a Rotor™ built with Tuff™ Molding could withstand a drop from a three-story building. Coupled with a water resistant coated board makes this hopper fully functional even underwater. Nothing you'll encounter on a paintball field could penetrate our Tuff Molding and cause your loader to break. 

Constant Feed

The Constant Feed Rate feature ensures a feed rate of over 50 balls per second, far exceeding pro level requirements. Rapid/Constant Feed is made possible by the combination of the Rotor™ Loader's constant feed rotor carousel, and the opposing rotation of the center rotor arm. The result is a smooth, consistent, rapid, and dependable feed performance. 

Rapid Reload

Rapid Reload makes reloading a quick and easy process. The Rotor™ has a transparent locking lid, integrated into an interchangeable dual density carrier, which allows for fast loading and a secure closure. The Rotor™ has a 200-ball capacity, 20% more than most competing loaders, and a revolutionary spring-loaded collapsing floor. Lastly, see-through windows make it easy to monitor your paint level. 

Toolless Maintenance

Tool-less Maintenance makes assembly and disassembly a rapid, highly intuitive, and effortless process. A simple slide of the locking tab and push of a button enables the breakdown of the loader for basic cleaning and maintenance. 

Sharkfin Jam Release Trigger

A simple squeeze of the Sharkfin Trigger, located on the underside of the Rotor™, releases the jammed paint immediately. 

BlackOps

No one wants to give his or her position away during night play. This unique feature enables you to turn the ON/OFF LED off during those night or low light games. 

Adjustable Torque

The Rotor allows you to fine tune your torque setting manually for any paint you encounter.
